{
  "id": 5074313831120896,
  "name": "Speculation rules: form_submission field",
  "summary": "This extends speculation rules syntax to allow developers to specify the form_submission field for prerender.\n\nThis field directs the browser to prepare the prerender as a form submission, so that it can be activated by real form submission navigations. Examples include a simple search form which results in a /search?q=XXX GET request navigation, support of which has been requested by web developers.",
